title: 5,10-Methenyltetrahydrofolate
text:
5,10-Methenyltetrahydrofolate (5,10-CH=THF) is a form of <a href="tetrahydrofolate">tetrahydrofolate</a> that is an intermediate in <a href="metabolism">metabolism</a>. 5,10-CH=THF is a <a href="coenzyme">coenzyme</a> that accepts and donates methenyl (CH=) groups. 
It is produced from <a href="5%2C10-methylenetetrahydrofolate">5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate</a> by either a <a href="methylenetetrahydrofolate%20dehydrogenase%20%28NAD%2B%29">NAD+ dependent methylenetetrahydrofolate dehydrogenase</a>, or a <a href="Methylenetetrahydrofolate%20dehydrogenase%20%28NADP%2B%29">NADP+ dependent dehydrogenase</a>. It can also be produced as an intermediate in <a href="histidine">histidine</a> catabolism, by <a href="formiminotransferase%20cyclodeaminase">formiminotransferase cyclodeaminase</a>, from <a href="5-formiminotetrahydrofolate">5-formiminotetrahydrofolate</a>.
5,10-CH=THF is a substrate for <a href="methenyltetrahydrofolate%20cyclohydrolase">methenyltetrahydrofolate cyclohydrolase</a>, which converts it into <a href="10-formyltetrahydrofolate">10-formyltetrahydrofolate</a>.
